name: Wes J Featured @ Escape Outdoors (Alderwood Mall)
description:
We are super stoked to introduce our NEWEST store to carry Wes J Clothing: Escape Outdoors (formally known as Helly Hansen)...located in the Alderwood Mall in Lynnwood, WA. 

They carry brands such as Mountain Hardware, Patagonia, Nixon, Vibram, North Face, Dakine, 686, Prana, Oakley, & numerous other quality, internationally knowon brands. 

This is a huge honor to be represent the locally hand-made, Pacific Northwest at it's finest in a larger city and high traffic location, in addition to being so close to Seattle, Bellevue, and other neighboring cities.

A big shout out to the Store Manager, Michael, and the Team, as well as Greg, one of the Co-Owners. We definitely invite you to visit Escape Outdoors in the Alderwood Mall...Get Yours. Rep It. Rock It.

Escape Outdoors will be carrying these specific designs:

 - Mount Baker Crewneck Sweatshirts
 - Seattleite Zip Hoodies
 - Seattliete Ladies & Mens Tees

name: Wes J Featured @ Seattle Magazine
description:
Wes J Clothing was featured in March 2010, Seattle Magazine, Day Trip Section...along with Four Starrs Boutique in Bellingham (Fairhaven), WA. We invite you to take a look at the article highlighting "Fairhaven's mix of modern trends with historic beauty."

"Located in the southern end of Bellingham, Fairhaven is a neighborhood that mixes modern trends with historic architecture. Founded in the late 1880s, this small, quaint community is filled with independently owned boutiques and restaurants, all just a short walk from the glistening waters of Bellingham Bay. "

name: Wes J Featured @ Mt. Baker Experience Magazine
description:
With a fortunate run-in with one of the owners of the Mount Baker Experience Magazine over the Holidays...we are very honored to be have a featured article written on the line and represent Whatcom County and beyond in their 25th Anniversary Issue. The magazine is available in REI, Yeagers Sporting Goods, Sportsman Chalet...just about... any "active" and "outdoorsy" shop from Vancouver, BC to Seattle, WA. Rock & Roll...Thank you friends and family for all the support...this one is for you. - Wes J

"Mount Baker Experience, a quarterly adventure publication focusing on the activities in the Mount Baker vicinity of Northwestern Washington and lower mainland B.C. Mount Baker Experience was founded in 1987. If you can see Mt. Baker from where you stand, you are part of the experience. There are 25,000 copies distributed to retailers, adventure outlets, travel sites, from Seattle to Vancouver every issue. 2011, marks its 25th year of publication. " - MBE

You are also able to check out the full article within the online edition by copying & paste the following link in your web browser: http://www.mountbakerexperience.com/02-11_article11.html

name: Wes J Featured @ AS Review Magazine (Western Washington University)
description:
We are very honored to be a featured local business along with a few other artists, within this article. Nick Markman, one of the Writers for the AS Review, did a great job highlighting the business's history and future plans of Wes J Clothing. We invite you to check out this press article at (you can also copy and paste this link in your web browser):

http://as.wwu.edu/asreview/homespun-threads/

About AS Review Magazine:

An organization designed and run by Western students, the Associated Students (AS) seeks to ensure a fulfilling college and academic experience for all university students through the many services, facilities and programs it offers. Whether interested in testing your skills as a DJ for campus radio station KUGS, craving a weekend in the mountains on an Outdoor Center excursion, or just curious about getting involved in student government or one of our two hundred clubs, the AS has the resources to assist you. By providing Western students with enjoyable networking and leadership opportunities, the AS attempts to help students define themselves, find allies in the community and engage in their university surroundings.
